    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "LSMR is MINRES specialized for solving least squares. Use LSMR to solve equations of the form "
            },
            {
              "type": "emphasis",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Ax = b"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " where an exact solution does not exist. The returned solution minimizes ‖"
            },
            {
              "type": "emphasis",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " b-Ax "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "‖₂."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Although LSMR is equivalent to MINRES applied to the normal equations "
            },
            {
              "type": "emphasis",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "A"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "emphasis",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "ᵀ"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "emphasis",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Ax = A"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "emphasis",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "ᵀ"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "emphasis",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "b"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " in exact arithmetic, it has superior numerical behavior and is preferred. Due to the implicit squaring of the condition of "
            },
            {
              "type": "emphasis",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "A"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " in the normal equations, LSMR may struggle to converge in single precision, and double precision arithmetic is recommended. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "For symmetric positive-definite systems, use "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/accelerate/2873527-sparseconjugategradient"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " instead. For square, full-rank unsymmetric or indefinite equations, use "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/accelerate/2873536-sparsegmres"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        }
      ]
    }
